This is a full-stack digital guestbook application. I will use **Next.js** for the framework because it allows us to handle both the frontend and the backend (Server Actions/API) in a single unified codebase with excellent performance.

### The Tech Stack

1.  **Framework:** [Next.js (App Router)](https://nextjs.org/) - Chosen for its built-in SEO optimization, Server Actions for form handling, and seamless deployment.
2.  **Styling:** [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) - Chosen for rapid UI development and small bundle sizes.
3.  **Database & ORM:** [Prisma](https://www.prisma.io/) with **PostgreSQL** (via Supabase or Vercel Postgres) - Chosen for type-safety and the ability to easily manage relational data.
4.  **Components:** [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) - High-quality, accessible components built on Radix UI.
5.  **Authentication:** [NextAuth.js](https://next-auth.js.org/) - The standard for authentication in the Next.js ecosystem.

---

### 1. Database Schema (`prisma/schema.prisma`)

We need a simple structure to hold guestbook entries and an admin user.

```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

model Message {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  name      String
  content   String   @db.Text
  approved  Boolean  @default(false) // For moderation
}

model User {
  id       String @id @default(cuid())
  email    String @unique
  password String // Hashed
}
```

---

### 2. Server Actions (`lib/actions.ts`)

Instead of traditional API endpoints, we'll use Next.js Server Actions for better security and a cleaner DX.

```typescript
"use server"

import { revalidatePath } from "next/cache";
import prisma from "./prisma"; // Shared prisma client instance

export async function submitMessage(formData: FormData) {
  const name = formData.get("name") as string;
  const content = formData.get("content") as string;

  if (!name || !content) return { error: "Fields are required" };

  await prisma.message.create({
    data: { name, content, approved: false },
  });

  revalidatePath("/");
  return { success: true };
}

export async function updateMessageStatus(id: string, approved: boolean) {
  // In a real app, verify the admin session here via getServerSession
  await prisma.message.update({
    where: { id },
    data: { approved },
  });

  revalidatePath("/admin");
  revalidatePath("/");
}

export async function deleteMessage(id: string) {
  await prisma.message.delete({ where: { id } });
  revalidatePath("/admin");
}
```

