To build a production-ready restaurant ordering application with real-time capabilities, we need a stack that handles high-frequency updates, state management, and a seamless user experience.

### The Tech Stack

| Component | Choice | Alternatives Considered | Why I picked it |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Framework** | **Next.js 14** | Vite + React, Remix | Next.js offers excellent SEO for your menu, built-in API routes, and optimized image handling. |
| **Styling** | **Tailwind CSS** | CSS Modules, Styled Components | Rapid UI development and small bundle sizes. |
| **Database/Backend** | **Supabase** | Firebase, AWS Amplify | Supabase provides a real-time Postgres database. Unlike Firebase, it allows for complex relational queries (essential for orders/items). |
| **State Management** | **Zustand** | Redux, Context API | Extremely lightweight and perfect for managing a shopping cart without boilerplate. |
| **Real-time** | **Postgres Changes** | Socket.io, Pusher | Built into Supabase; no need to manage a separate WebSocket server. |

