### 1. The Database Schema (`prisma/schema.prisma`)

In this model, we don't "create" new tables or indexes dynamically at runtime (which is a security and performance risk). Instead, we ensure the schema is optimized with **Composite Indexes** so that queries for any specific tenant are lightning-fast.

```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

model Company {
  id        String     @id @default(uuid())
  name      String     @unique
  slug      String     @unique
  categories Category[]
  createdAt DateTime   @default(now())
}

model Category {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  name      String
  companyId String
  company   Company  @relation(fields: [companyId], references: [id])

  // These are the critical indexes for multi-tenancy
  @@index([companyId]) 
  @@index([companyId, name]) // Speeds up lookups within a tenant
}
```

