### 2. Preventing Overbooking (Database Function)
To ensure we never exceed capacity, we use a PostgreSQL function. This is more reliable than checking the count in the frontend.

```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION join_event(target_event_id UUID, target_user_id UUID)
RETURNS void AS $$
DECLARE
    current_count INTEGER;
    max_capacity INTEGER;
BEGIN
    -- Get current capacity and count
    SELECT capacity INTO max_capacity FROM events WHERE id = target_event_id;
    SELECT COUNT(*) INTO current_count FROM rsvps WHERE event_id = target_event_id;

    -- Check if spots are available
    IF current_count < max_capacity THEN
        INSERT INTO rsvps (event_id, user_id) VALUES (target_event_id, target_user_id);
    ELSE
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'Event is full';
    END IF;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;
```

