### 4. Background Synchronization (Persistence)

Writing to PostgreSQL on every single API call would crash the database under high load. Instead, we "Sync" Redis usage back to Postgres every minute or after a threshold.

```typescript
// src/services/sync-service.ts
import { redis } from '../lib/redis';
import { prisma } from '../lib/db';

export async function syncUsageToDb() {
  // Use SCAN to find all usage keys without blocking Redis
  const stream = redis.scanStream({ match: 'tenant:usage:*' });

  for await (const keys of stream) {
    for (const key of keys) {
      const apiKey = key.split(':')[2];
      const usage = await redis.get(key);

      if (usage) {
        await prisma.tenant.update({
          where: { apiKey },
          data: { currentUsage: parseInt(usage) }
        });
      }
    }
  }
  console.log('Usage synced to Postgres.');
}

// In a real app, run this as a cron job or a separate worker process
setInterval(syncUsageToDb, 60000); 
```

