### 1. The Database Schema (`schema.prisma`)

In a multi-tenant app, every record must be tied to an `organizationId`. We use Clerk's Organization IDs as our "Source of Truth" for multi-tenancy.

```prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

enum EquipmentStatus {
  AVAILABLE
  IN_USE
  MAINTENANCE
  LOST
}

model Equipment {
  id             String          @id @default(cuid())
  name           String
  serialNumber   String?
  category       String?
  status         EquipmentStatus @default(AVAILABLE)

  // Multi-tenancy: Every item belongs to a Clerk Organization
  organizationId String          @index

  // Tracking
  assignedToId   String?         // Clerk User ID
  assignedToName String?         // For easy display

  createdAt      DateTime        @default(now())
  updatedAt      DateTime        @updatedAt

  @@index([organizationId])
}
```

