### 1. The Data Model (Prisma)

The key to a dynamic form builder is how we store the "Schema" of the form. We will use a relational structure for the Form but a JSON structure for the specific fields to allow for maximum flexibility without constant migrations.

```prisma
// schema.prisma

model Form {
  id          String       @id @default(cuid())
  createdAt   DateTime     @default(now())
  title       String
  description String?
  published   Boolean      @default(false)

  // JSON structure: Array of {id, type, label, placeholder, required, options[]}
  content     Json         

  submissions Submission[]
  userId      String       // Connect to your Auth provider
}

model Submission {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
