### 1. Database Schema Design (Prisma)

The core challenge is linking translations. We use a **Canonical Model**: one entry is the "source" or "master," and all other versions link back to it.

```prisma
// prisma/schema.prisma

enum ContentStatus {
  DRAFT
  PUBLISHED
  ARCHIVED
}

model Content {
  id              String         @id @default(uuid())
  slug            String         // Shared identifier (e.g., "how-to-bake-bread")
  locale          String         // e.g., "en-US", "en-GB", "fr-FR"
  title           String
  body            String         @db.Text
  status          ContentStatus  @default(DRAFT)

  // Self-referencing relationship
  canonicalId     String?        // If null, this is the original/master version
  canonical       Content?       @relation("Translations", fields: [canonicalId], references: [id])
  translations    Content[]      @relation("Translations")

  createdAt       DateTime       @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime       @updatedAt

  @@unique([slug, locale])       // Unique constraint for content-locale pairs
  @@index([canonicalId])
}
```

