### 1. Database Schema (PostgreSQL)

To perform radius searches efficiently, we use the `geography` type provided by the **PostGIS** extension.

```sql
-- Enable PostGIS extension
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS postgis;

-- Users Table
CREATE TABLE "User" (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  location GEOGRAPHY(Point, 4326) -- 4326 is the standard GPS coordinate system (WGS84)
);

-- Events Table
CREATE TABLE "Event" (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  location GEOGRAPHY(Point, 4326)
);

-- Create Spatial Indexes for performance
CREATE INDEX user_location_idx ON "User" USING GIST (location);
CREATE INDEX event_location_idx ON "Event" USING GIST (location);
```

