### 3. Backend Implementation (NestJS)

We need a "Gateway" to handle real-time location updates via WebSockets.

#### Location Gateway (`src/fleet/fleet.gateway.ts`)
```typescript
@WebSocketGateway({ cors: true })
export class FleetGateway {
  @WebSocketServer()
  server: Server;

  // This method is called by vehicle IoT devices or driver mobile apps
  @SubscribeMessage('updateLocation')
  async handleLocationUpdate(@MessageBody() data: { vehicleId: string, lat: number, lng: number }) {
    // 1. Update database (async)
    // 2. Broadcast to all dashboard clients
    this.server.emit('locationUpdated', data);
  }
