### 1. Database Architecture (The "Hybrid" Approach)

We will use a relational structure for core patient data and a `JSONB` column for specialty-specific metadata. This is superior to the EAV (Entity-Attribute-Value) pattern which is notoriously difficult to query and slow at scale.

```prisma
// schema.prisma

model Patient {
  id            String    @id @default(cuid())
  firstName     String
  lastName      String
  dateOfBirth   DateTime
  records       Record[]
  createdAt     DateTime  @default(now())
}

model Record {
  id            String    @id @default(cuid())
  patientId     String
  patient       Patient   @relation(fields: [patientId], references: [id])
  specialty     Specialty
  providerId    String

  // The "Variable Fields" magic:
  // This stores JSON like: { "heartRate": 72, "rhythm": "Sinus" }
  clinicalData  Json      

  notes         String?   @db.Text
  createdAt     DateTime  @default(now())
}

enum Specialty {
  CARDIOLOGY
  DERMATOLOGY
  GENERAL_PRACTICE
  ONCOLOGY
}
```

