### 1. Database Schema (Prisma)

We need to store events with a `geography` type (supported by PostGIS) and a list of interests.

```prisma
// schema.prisma
datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client-js"
}

model User {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  email     String   @unique
  interests String[] // e.g., ["techno", "coding", "hiking"]
}

model Event {
  id            String   @id @default(cuid())
  title         String
  description   String
  location      Unsupported("geography(Point, 4326)") // PostGIS Point type
  interests     String[] // e.g., ["techno", "nightlife"]
  checkInCount  Int      @default(0)
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())

  @@index([location], name: "location_idx", type: Gist)
}
```

