### The Tech Stack

| Component | Choice | Alternatives | Why? |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Language** | **TypeScript** | JavaScript, Go | Provides type safety which is critical for complex data structures like nested categories. |
| **Framework** | **NestJS** | Express, Fastify | Offers a structured, modular architecture out-of-the-box. Excellent for maintainable production apps. |
| **Database** | **PostgreSQL** | MongoDB, MySQL | Better for relational data integrity. PostgreSQL’s **JSONB** column type is the perfect middle-ground for handling "variable attributes." |
| **ORM** | **Prisma** | TypeORM, Sequelize | Type-safe queries and easy-to-read migrations. Handles nested relations more intuitively than most. |
| **API Docs** | **Swagger** | Redoc | Built-in support in NestJS for auto-generating OpenAPI documentation. |

