### Phase 3: Crucial Features for "Production-Ready"

#### A. Geo-Fencing for Interactions
To prevent users from "spoofing" or commenting on pins from across the world, the backend should validate the user's distance before accepting a comment.

```javascript
// Supabase Edge Function (Node.js)
export const postComment = async (req) => {
  const { user_id, pin_id, message, user_lat, user_lng } = req.body;

  // Check if user is actually within 50m of the pin
  const { data: isNear } = await supabase.rpc('check_proximity', {
    p_id: pin_id,
    u_lat: user_lat,
    u_lng: user_lng,
    dist: 50 // meters
  });

  if (!isNear) {
    throw new Error("You are too far away to interact with this drop!");
  }

  // Proceed with inserting comment...
}
